Unknown gunmen have reportedly killed four officials of the National Drug Law Enforcement Agency (NDLEA), Ifon Division at a check point along Ikaro/ Sabo road in Ondo state. The gunmen, three in number, carried out the operation with a motorcycle. They also burnt the operations vehicle of the NDLEA officials. Reports say the NDLEA officers were five in number at the check point but only one of them escaped and their rifles were taken away. Gunmen ambushed and killed three officials of the National Drug Law Enforcement Agency (NDLEA) in Okene Local Government Area of Kogi State. The victims are Onwumere Nicholas, Peter Ebun and Abdulrahman Musa. The attack occurred about 8.30p.m. on Friday when six officers of the agency were on duty at one… In "Metro and Crime" Suspected gunmen yesterday killed an operative of the National Drug Law Enforcement Agency (NDLEA), Mr Tanko Amfani, by some suspected drug traffickers. In the same vein, the gunmen injured three officials of the agency who were on duty around the city. Chairman of the NDLEA, Col. Mohammad Mustapha Abdullah (rtd),… In "News" A Heavy mounted roadblock by unknown gunmen have killed and operative of National Drug Law Enforcement Agency (NDLEA) while approaching the scene. In the same vein, the gunmen injured three officials of the Drug Law Enforcement who were on duty around the city. The development which was hinted by the… In "News"